# SAFETY_POLICY.profile.md - python_cli

## Purpose

Define Python CLI safety defaults.

## Private Data

- Use synthetic fixtures only.
- Do not commit private raw input, secrets, tokens, .env contents, or local credential files.
- Do not paste real command output containing sensitive paths or values into docs.

## Side Effects

- CLI commands should default to read-only or dry-run behavior when possible.
- File writes require explicit output paths and expected change review.
- External API mutation is out of scope unless explicitly approved by the target project contract.

## Logging

Logs and examples must redact or avoid credentials, private inputs, and user-specific paths.
